Setup - Run these on your GCP console/terminal

1. Give your SA the roles it needs

1. PROJECT_ID="project-8f3b3c8e-4647-4878-8b5"
SA_EMAIL="github-terraform@${PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com"

2. gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding $PROJECT_ID \
  --member="serviceAccount:${SA_EMAIL}" \
  --role="roles/compute.admin"

3. gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding $PROJECT_ID \
  --member="serviceAccount:${SA_EMAIL}" \
  --role="roles/iam.serviceAccountUser"

4. gcloud projects add-iam-policy-binding $PROJECT_ID \
  --member="serviceAccount:${SA_EMAIL}" \
  --role="roles/storage.admin"


2. Attach the SA to your Jenkins VM


Replace jenkins and us-central1-a with your VM name + zone:bash



1. gcloud compute instances stop jenkins --zone=us-central1-a

2. gcloud compute instances set-service-account jenkins \
  --zone=us-central1-a \
  --service-account=${SA_EMAIL} \
  --scopes=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform

3. gcloud compute instances start jenkins --zone=us-central1-a





3. Verify from inside the Jenkins VM
SSH into the VM and run:

gcloud auth list


You should see github-terraform@project-8f3b3c8e-4647-4878-8b5.iam.gserviceaccount.com as ACTIVE.






